        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 5:42PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 542 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Wheeless, or 18 miles northeast of Clayton, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Black Mesa Park and Wheeless.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
